#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:122
msgid "Style guide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:124
msgid ""
"This section has a few very brief recommendations to help authors use common "
"style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:126
msgid ""
"In terms of contributions, we value your coding and content writing far more "
"than perfect prose! Just do your best, and then :ref:`ask for editorial "
"review <contact>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:128
msgid "**Spelling:** Where possible use US-English spelling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:130
msgid ""
"**Avoid idiomatic expressions**: These can be particularly confusing to non-"
"native speakers (for example \"putting your foot in your mouth\" actually "
"means \"saying something embarrassing\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:132
msgid "**Emphasis:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:134
msgid ""
"**Bold** : use for file names, and UI/menu instructions (for example: "
"\"Press **OK** to do something\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:135
msgid ""
"*Italic* : use for tool names - e.g. *Clang*, *emcc*, *Closure Compiler*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:136
msgid ""
"``monotype`` : use for inline code (where you can't link to the API "
"reference) and for demonstrating tool command line options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:138
msgid "Other than the above rules, emphasis should be used sparingly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:141
msgid ""
"**Lists**: Use a colon on the lead-in to the list where appropriate. "
"Capitalize the first letter and use a full-stop for each item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:145
msgid "How to link to a document or heading"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:147
msgid ""
"To link to a page, first define a globally unique reference before the page "
"title (e.g. ``_my-page-reference``) then link to it using the `ref <http://"
"sphinx-doc.org/markup/inline.html#ref-role>`_ role as shown: ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:160
msgid ""
"This is a better approach than linking to documents using the *:doc:* role, "
"because the links do not get broken if the articles are moved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:162
msgid ""
"This approach is also recommended for linking to arbitrary headings in the "
"site."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/about.rst:164
msgid ""
"There are a number of other roles that are useful for linking — including "
"`Sphinx Domains <http://sphinx-doc.org/domains.html>`_ for linking to code "
"items, and **term** for linking to glossary terms."
msgstr ""

